TODO [1] 2026-4-7
===================================================================================================================
    Replace linear lookup tables with hash tables in decode.c to optimize instruction decoding.
===================================================================================================================
    Performance profiling with perf shows that decode_instr_info is the top performance bottleneck,
    consuming ~41% of total CPU time.The current linear search over instruction tables results in O(n)
    time complexity, which is inefficient, especially for real-world workloads.

    Although DBCache already outperforms the naive loop in real programs (e.g., count_words.lua), decoding
    remains expensive.By implementing two hash tables (for normal/RVC instructions), we reduce decoding
    complexity to O(1), which will further boost overall simulator performance.
===================================================================================================================
